=head1 DESCRIPTION

The processing rules for when a registration can be associated with an
origination identity and disassociated from an origination identity.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> AssociationBehavior => Str

The association behavior.

=over

=item *

C<ASSOCIATE_BEFORE_SUBMIT> The origination identity has to be supplied
when creating a registration.

=item *

C<ASSOCIATE_ON_APPROVAL> This applies to all sender ID registrations.
The sender ID will be automatically provisioned once the registration
is approved.

=item *

C<ASSOCIATE_AFTER_COMPLETE> This applies to phone number registrations
when you must complete a registration first, then associate one or more
phone numbers later. For example 10DLC campaigns and long codes.

=back



=head2 B<REQUIRED> DisassociationBehavior => Str

The disassociation behavior.

=over

=item *

C<DISASSOCIATE_ALL_CLOSES_REGISTRATION> All origination identities must
be disassociated from the registration before the registration can be
closed.

=item *

C<DISASSOCIATE_ALL_ALLOWS_DELETE_REGISTRATION> All origination
identities must be disassociated from the registration before the
registration can be deleted.

=item *

C<DELETE_REGISTRATION_DISASSOCIATES> The registration can be deleted
and all origination identities will be disasscoiated.

=back



=head2 IsoCountryCode => Str

The two-character code, in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 format, for the country
or region.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> ResourceType => Str

Defines the behavior of when an origination identity and registration
can be associated with each other.



